For further identification check fingerprint.^$ $ $aFingerprint : 159308 - a1 *2 eri : a2 3*3 docere$ - b1 A du : b2 3C3 odiu,$^$ $ $aThe 'Promptvarium' was reprinted several times after the original edition of 1593 but the imprint of all these editions was left unchanged. All editions are therefore dated 1593. These editions are listed partially in: Dirk Imhof, Jan Moretus and the continuation of the Plantin Press (Leiden, 2014), S-49. Imhof gives a number of characteristics by which different editions can be distinguished but the list (5 editions of the 'Pars hyemalis' and 5 of the 'Pars aestivalis'). Individual copies combine characteristics of two editions, probably because preliminary gatherings and body were combined in different ways. This editions combines the characteristics of the preliminaries of Imhof's edition D with the body of edition A or B

column29: ^$0$0$aDe visibili monarchia ecclesiæ, libri VIII. In quibus diligens instituitur disputatio de certa & perpetua ecclesiæ, Dei tum succeβione, tum gubernatione monarchica, ab ipso mundi initio usque ad finem. Deinde etiam civitatis diaboli persaepè interrupta progressio proponitur, sectaeque omnes & haereses confutantur, quae unquam contra veram fidem emerserunt. Denique de antichristo ipso & membris eius, deque vera Dei & adulterina diabioli ecclesia, copisè tractatur. Si quid praeterea difficile & scopulosum vel in Pontificum Romanorum historia, vel in conciliorum generalium ratione accidit idipsum ex propositio discutitur & examinatur. Cum indice rerum & personarum locuplete$ $ $cAuctore Nicolao Sandero [...]
